ConversationSession Architecture:
- active_entities: jsonb, capped at MAX_ENTITIES, FIFO eviction via evict_oldest!
- conversation_history: jsonb, capped at MAX_HISTORY msgs, truncated to MAX_MSG_LENGTH chars
- current_procedure: jsonb, default {} — stores step-by-step procedure state when active
- session_status: "active" | "in_procedure" — controls TTL and message routing behavior
- Session TTL: EXPIRY_MINUTES (dynamic — extended during active procedures). Refreshed on each interaction.
- find_or_create_for: destroys expired, creates new. Unique index on [identifier, channel]
- Dedup: find_entity_by_name_or_alias (case-insensitive on keys, wa_filename, aliases)
Entity extraction_methods (ordered by quality):
  haiku_doc_refs > chunk_aliases > pending_first_query > filename_only > filename_from_text
EntityExtractorService flow:
  1. Primary: doc_refs present → register_from_doc_refs → promote or add_entity_with_aliases
  2. Fallback: no doc_refs → register_from_citation_filenames → add_entity
  3. promote_pending_entity: ALWAYS preserve wa_filename when old starts with "wa_"
SessionContextBuilder.build(session) → String injected into generation prompt:
  - ## Session Focus (entities with type + aliases)
  - ## Recent Conversation (last 3 turns)
Tests create sessions programmatically (no fixtures for conversation_sessions)
